15 obtained before services are provided through telehealth;
16 (b) Ensure that the confidentiality of the client's medical information is
17 maintained as required by this chapter and other applicable state and federal
18 law. At a minimum, confidentiality shall be maintained through appropriate
19 processes, practices, and technology that conform to applicable state and
20 federal law, including but not limited to the Health Insurance Portability and
21 Accountability Act of 1996, Pub. L. No. 104-191, as amended;
22 (c) Ensure that telehealth services are accessible to clients with disabilities in
23 compliance with Section 508 of the Rehabilitation Act of 1973, as amended,
24 29 U.S.C. sec. 794(d), Title III of the Americans with Disabilities Act, 42
25 U.S.C. secs. 12181 to 12189, and all other applicable federal and state
26 accessibility requirements;
27 (d) Disclose to the client the potential risks to privacy and confidentiality of
