8 (4) For purposes of this section:
9 (a) "Client" means:
10 1. An individual, family, or group who receives social work services from a
11 social worker;
12 2. A corporate entity or other organization, if the social worker is contracted to
13 provide a social work service of benefit directly to the corporate entity or
14 organization; or
15 3. A legal guardian who is responsible for making decisions regarding the
16 provision of social work services to a minor or legally incompetent adult;
17 (b) "Social worker" means an individual licensed as a:
18 1. Certified social worker pursuant to KRS 335.080;
19 2. Licensed social worker pursuant to KRS 335.090; or
20 3. Licensed clinical social worker pursuant to KRS 335.100; and
21 (c) "Telehealth" means the use of interactive audio, video, or other electronic
22 media to deliver health care. It includes the use of electronic media for
23 diagnosis, consultation, treatment, transfer of health or medical data, and
24 continuing education].
